modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529977\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529977\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mlx1665702995827.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mlx1665702995827.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mlx1665702995827.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mlx1665702995827\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Install the WRD in the Application Server\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can now deploy the WAR file (<span class=\"ph filepath\">wrd.war</span>) you created earlier. See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qnb1665702995328.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qnb1665702995328.html\" title=\"The IBM Integrated Web application server for i can deploy applications that are in the form of a web archive file, .war file or a web application bundle .wab file. The Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) servlet is not in this format, so it must be packaged into a .war file.\">Configure the WRD and Create a wrd.war File on iSeries</a>.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__li_d29390e1_d29391e1_d29392e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__p_d66818e1_d66819e1_d66820e1\">Transfer the <span class=\"ph filepath\">wrd.war</span> file to\n               the iSeries IFS. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">If the <span class=\"ph filepath\">wrd.war</span> file is not located on the iSeries IFS,\n               transfer it to an IFS directory now, using binary FTP, or drag and drop in the\n               Windows Explorer, to a shared IFS directory.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__li_d29393e1_d29394e1_d29395e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__p_d66821e1_d66822e1_d66823e1\">On the IBM Web Administration for i page, select\n               the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Manage</code> tab. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">There are four additional tabs under the top tabs.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__li_d29396e1_d29397e1_d29398e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Application Servers</code> tab, select the newly-created application server in <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Server</span>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__li_d29399e1_d29400e1_d29401e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__p_d66824e1_d66825e1_d66826e1\">On the left pane, under <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Application\n                  Server Wizards</span>, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Install New Application</span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">On the right side, the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Install New Application</span> page\n               appears. It has only one edit box and a browse button.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__li_d29402e1_d29403e1_d29404e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__p_d66827e1_d66828e1_d66829e1\">Enter or browse for the fully qualified, absolute\n               path to the <span class=\"ph filepath\">wrd.war</span> file in the IFS. Then click\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Next</span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Now you are asked for the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">application name</span>, which is\n                     <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">wrd</span>, and for the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Context root</span>.\n                  This is the part of the URL that immediately follows the machine name and port\n                  number. For example, if you want the Uniface WRD to be accessed with a URL that\n                  has the following form:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__p_d66830e1_d66831e1_d66832e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">http://</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">iSeriesNetworkName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">:10000/uniface/</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__p_d66833e1_d66834e1_d66835e1\">then <code class=\"ph codeph\">/uniface</code>would be the\n                  context root. When finished click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Next</span>. </p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__li_d29405e1_d29406e1_d29407e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__p_d66836e1_d66837e1_d66838e1\">On the next screen accept the defaults by\n               clicking <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Next</span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Now you will see a summary of what you filled in.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__li_d29408e1_d29409e1_d29410e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__p_d66839e1_d66840e1_d66841e1\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Finish</span> to start the\n               installation of the <span class=\"ph filepath\">wrd.war</span> file. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">A new page is displayed, with a list of all applications currently installed in\n                  the application server. The <span class=\"ph filepath\">wrd</span> is among them, but in front\n                  of it is a yellow bullet with an hourglass symbol, indicating that its\n                  installation is in progress.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mlx1665702995827__p_d66842e1_d66843e1_d66844e1\">Again, depending on your machine type and its\n                  workload, this might take some time to complete. When it has completed, the yellow\n                  bullet changes to red, indicating that it is installed but not running, or to\n                  green, indicating that it is installed and running.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529977\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529977\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Install the WRD in the Application Server Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Install the WRD in the Application Server You can now deploy the WAR file ( wrd.war ) you created earlier. See Configure the WRD and Create a wrd.war File on iSeries . Transfer the wrd.war file to the iSeries IFS. If the wrd.war file is not located on the iSeries IFS, transfer it to an IFS directory now, using binary FTP, or drag and drop in the Windows Explorer, to a shared IFS directory. On the IBM Web Administration for i page, select the Manage tab. There are four additional tabs under the top tabs. In the Application Servers tab, select the newly-created application server in Server . On the left pane, under Application Server Wizards , click Install New Application . On the right side, the Install New Application page appears. It has only one edit box and a browse button. Enter or browse for the fully qualified, absolute path to the wrd.war file in the IFS. Then click Next . Now you are asked for the application name , which is wrd , and for the Context root . This is the part of the URL that immediately follows the machine name and port number. For example, if you want the Uniface WRD to be accessed with a URL that has the following form: http:// iSeriesNetworkName :10000/uniface/ then /uniface would be the context root. When finished click Next . On the next screen accept the defaults by clicking Next . Now you will see a summary of what you filled in. Click Finish to start the installation of the wrd.war file. A new page is displayed, with a list of all applications currently installed in the application server. The wrd is among them, but in front of it is a yellow bullet with an hourglass symbol, indicating that its installation is in progress. Again, depending on your machine type and its workload, this might take some time to complete. When it has completed, the yellow bullet changes to red, indicating that it is installed but not running, or to green, indicating that it is installed and running. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}